LORE midgaard-guard
FLAGS MIDGAARD GUARD
- Seven Watches: Kindling (dawn) → Ash (curfew); Lantern Watch is when patrols
  intensify and reliquary routes tighten; Ash Watch = ward inspectors and
  janitorial labor, not safe for strangers without a lodging chit
- Arrest warrants require Ledgerhouse seal; summary detention allowed up to
  one watch cycle without warrant
- The Breach Tower at the Lantern Registry: all inquiries deferred to the
  Ledgerhouse; guards are instructed not to speculate about its contents
- The Gloamvault, the Dungeon, and subterranean passages below the city are
  not fully controlled; the city does not officially acknowledge access routes
- Reckoning faction sympathizers sometimes probe guards about archived records;
  standard response: "Refer to the Ledgerhouse."
- Road warden patrol schedules posted at the north and east gates; gap coverage
  by contracted adventurer companies; coordination through Guard Command
~
